6
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:38,235
[MONKEY SCREECHES]

7
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,912
[HIGH-PITCHED GROWLING]

8
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:15,793
WOMAN: Poor baby.
It's a tough way to start out.

9
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,353
We'll give her 50-50.

10
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:19,598
What do you think, doc?

11
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:22,155
I say she'll make it.
Maybe,

12
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:25,557
with the help
of a future veterinarian.

13
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:33,510
Once she's off the bottle, of course.
Oh, I know, I know.

14
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:37,597
So, cub, what's
your name gonna be?

15
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:40,869
Careful, Val. She can't become a pet.

16
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:44,874
Mom, give me a little credit.
I'm practically a professional already.

17
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:47,196
You're practically in love already.

18
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,674
I know that look.

19
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:52,633
We might as well name her.
She's gonna be here for...

20
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:56,276
For as short a time as possible.
Until I place her, right, Val?

21
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:57,839
Well, she still needs a name.

22
00:01:58,080 --> 00:02:01,117
Call her Elsa. What else?

23
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,350
Elsa?

24
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,318
[CHUCKLES]

25
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:10,035
Elsa. Of course.

26
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:12,910
Elsa.

27
